ckdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527904\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104glm1665702575208.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/glm1665702575208.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/glm1665702575208.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"glm1665702575208\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Using Structs for Disconnected Record Sets\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Structs can be used to hold disconnected record sets, providing an alternative to the use of XML.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glm1665702575208__p_d17915e1_d17916e1_d17917e1\">When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">componentToStruct</span> is used with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/reconnecttags</span> switch, it generates a Struct that includes tags containing the occurrence metadata that is required to reconnect the data after using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">structToComponent</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dvf1665702566367.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dvf1665702566367.html\" title=\"To manage the exchange of data between components and a database, metadata is maintained about occurrences, such as whether the occurrence is new or already stored in a database. This occurs transparently, so that a programmer generally does not have to handle data state.\">Occurrence Metadata for Reconnect</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yio1665702575286.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yio1665702575286.html\" title=\"When converting between Uniface components and Structs using componentToStruct and structToComponent, you can set and retrieve annotations that provide information about the type of Uniface object and reconnect processing information for occurrences.\">Struct Annotations for Uniface Component Data</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glm1665702575208__p_d17918e1_d17919e1_d17920e1\">It is possible to update and manipulate the generated Struct, updating occurrences, adding new fields, and manually changing tags. However, when the modified Struct is loaded into the component with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">structToComponent</span>, any Struct nodes that cannot be mapped to a corresponding fields, occurrences, or entities will be ignored, as will their tags.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glm1665702575208__p_d17921e1_d17922e1_d17923e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zom1665702566196.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zom1665702566196.html\" title=\"Disconnected record sets provide a way for components to maintain and share data and its state (such as whether the data has been modified) even when a connection to a database is not available. They are typically used for communication between web components (server pages and web services) and are usually implemented as XML, JSON, or Uniface Structs.\">Disconnected Record Sets</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yio1665702575286.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Struct Annotations for Uniface Component Data</a><p>When converting between Uniface components and Structs using componentToStruct and structToComponent, you can set and retrieve annotations that provide information about the type of Uniface object and reconnect processing information for occurrences.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dvf1665702566367.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Occurrence Metadata for Reconnect</a><p>To manage the exchange of data between components and a database, metadata is maintained about occurrences, such as whether the occurrence is new or already stored in a database. This occurs transparently, so that a programmer generally does not have to handle data state.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kpa1665702574811.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Reconnect Process</a><p>The reconnect process merges data in disconnected occurrences (in XML, JSON, or Structs) with data in the component, and resolves the state information that is stored in the modification status attributes. It removes duplicates of occurrences, removes occurrences marked for deletion from the component, and sets the appropriate modification flags.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lln1665702574971.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>structToComponent</a><p>Converts data from a Struct or collection of Structs into the entities and occurrences in the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/efi1719389270623.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>componentToStruct</a><p>Writes component data to a Struct.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527904\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527904\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Using Structs for Disconnected Record Sets Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Using Structs for Disconnected Record Sets Structs can be used to hold disconnected record sets, providing an alternative to the use of XML. When componentToStruct is used with the /reconnecttags switch, it generates a Struct that includes tags containing the occurrence metadata that is required to reconnect the data after using structToComponent . For more information, see Occurrence Metadata for Reconnect and Struct Annotations for Uniface Component Data . It is possible to update and manipulate the generated Struct, updating occurrences, adding new fields, and manually changing tags. However, when the modified Struct is loaded into the component with structToComponent , any Struct nodes that cannot be mapped to a corresponding fields, occurrences, or entities will be ignored, as will their tags. For more information, see Disconnected Record Sets . Related Links Struct Annotations for Uniface Component Data When converting between Uniface components and Structs using componentToStruct and structToComponent, you can set and retrieve annotations that provide information about the type of Uniface object and reconnect processing information for occurrences. Occurrence Metadata for Reconnect To manage the exchange of data between components and a database, metadata is maintained about occurrences, such as whether the occurrence is new or already stored in a database. This occurs transparently, so that a programmer generally does not have to handle data state. Reconnect Process The reconnect process merges data in disconnected occurrences (in XML, JSON, or Structs) with data in the component, and resolves the state information that is stored in the modification status attributes. It removes duplicates of occurrences, removes occurrences marked for deletion from the component, and sets the appropriate modification flags. structToComponent Converts data from a Struct or collection of Structs into the entities and occurrences in the component. componentToStruct Writes component data to a Struct. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}